38:07.320 --> 38:09.679
18 years.

38:09.680 --> 38:11.159
Children?

38:11.160 --> 38:14.199
Six.

38:14.200 --> 38:16.039
Yeah, six.

38:16.040 --> 38:18.479
I would've had more,
but it took me a while

38:18.480 --> 38:20.839
to get pregnant.

38:20.840 --> 38:22.879
Really.

38:22.880 --> 38:24.799
Well.

38:24.800 --> 38:26.047
Why don't you...

38:27.400 --> 38:28.719
make yourself comfortable?

38:28.720 --> 38:30.445
Take your time, and...

38:31.960 --> 38:33.679
I'll wait in the loo.

38:33.680 --> 38:37.168
Get undressed, and you
tell me when you're ready.

40:16.240 --> 40:18.439
Are you all right?

40:18.440 --> 40:20.881
Mm-hmm.

40:25.480 --> 40:28.809
May I take the sheet off?

40:29.640 --> 40:32.286
Mm-hmm.

42:29.760 --> 42:31.399
(DOVI) You know that guy?

42:31.400 --> 42:32.919
(DENNY) What guy?

42:32.920 --> 42:35.759
(DOVI)
The little guy with the glasses.

42:35.760 --> 42:37.759
He's been there over an hour.

42:37.760 --> 42:39.919
Maybe he's trying to get a tan.

42:39.920 --> 42:43.090
And who are you?

42:45.880 --> 42:48.399
Shomrim. What is that?

42:48.400 --> 42:50.439
Neighborhood patrol.

42:50.440 --> 42:54.645
Sometimes we go beyond.

43:01.640 --> 43:04.161
(SOBBING)

43:08.920 --> 43:11.599
Here.

43:11.600 --> 43:14.531
Drink some water.

43:25.440 --> 43:28.644
Thank you.

43:34.280 --> 43:37.479
Okay? You all right?

43:37.480 --> 43:41.679
Yes.

43:41.680 --> 43:44.531
It's just...

43:46.320 --> 43:49.046
No one... no one has...

43:51.320 --> 43:54.399
for so long.

43:54.400 --> 43:55.719
No one has...

43:55.720 --> 43:59.679
Since... Since your husband.

43:59.680 --> 44:02.884
No, not him.

44:06.400 --> 44:10.359
Touched me.

44:10.360 --> 44:13.530
No one has touched me.

44:46.440 --> 44:49.325
No, no. You get up front.

44:51.520 --> 44:54.564
Thank you.

45:05.240 --> 45:06.719
Fior, how're you doing?

45:06.720 --> 45:08.439
All right.

45:08.440 --> 45:10.119
What'll it be?

45:10.120 --> 45:13.039
The usual.

45:13.040 --> 45:15.039
Heavy on the potatoes.

45:15.040 --> 45:16.879
Two eggs, scrambled soft.

45:16.880 --> 45:19.119
Whole wheat toast, egg cream.

45:19.120 --> 45:20.845
Vanilla!

45:22.080 --> 45:23.759
(DOVI) So...

45:23.760 --> 45:26.850
Denny tells me you're
a good plumber.

45:28.320 --> 45:31.479
Yeah, I do a little.

45:31.480 --> 45:34.319
That's good. I got a job.

45:34.320 --> 45:38.079
I could maybe use someone
who could do a little...

45:38.080 --> 45:39.719
plumbing.

45:39.720 --> 45:42.119
You got a card?

45:42.120 --> 45:44.527
No.

45:48.440 --> 45:50.881
Write.

45:59.120 --> 46:02.642
Thanks. I'll be in touch.

46:28.520 --> 46:30.119
Hey, there.

46:30.120 --> 46:31.479
Hey.

46:31.480 --> 46:34.319
The world's a mysterious place.

46:34.320 --> 46:36.839
Mm-hmm.

46:36.840 --> 46:38.279
You didn't see us over there?

46:38.280 --> 46:39.959
I was listening to the music.

46:39.960 --> 46:42.799
Mm-hmm.

46:42.800 --> 46:45.039
I'm with my husband.

46:45.040 --> 46:47.039
Claude?

46:47.040 --> 46:48.799
You remembered.

46:48.800 --> 46:51.039
Tell him I said hi.

46:51.040 --> 46:54.005
Oh, he's the jealous type.

46:56.240 --> 46:59.199
It's my birthday.

46:59.200 --> 47:01.767
Happy birthday.

47:47.800 --> 47:50.439
(PHONE RINGING)

47:50.440 --> 47:53.239
(WOMEN) The number you have
reached is not in service.

47:53.240 --> 47:55.239
Please check the
number and dial again.

47:55.240 --> 47:57.124
Thank you.

48:29.080 --> 48:31.319
- Avigal.
- Dovi.

48:31.320 --> 48:32.799
You look very nice.

48:32.800 --> 48:34.119
Thank you.

48:34.120 --> 48:36.239
- Where are you going?
- To the city.

48:36.240 --> 48:39.079
Ah. The city? What for?

48:39.080 --> 48:41.279
Doctor's appointment.

48:41.280 --> 48:42.839
You need a lift? I...

48:42.840 --> 48:44.639
I can give you a
lift in the patrol.

48:44.640 --> 48:47.159
No thank you.
I'll take the train.

48:47.160 --> 48:48.959
It's okay. I'll read my book.

48:48.960 --> 48:51.639
You know, every time
I speak with you,

48:51.640 --> 48:54.319
it feels like you're
always in a rush.

48:54.320 --> 48:55.759
Maybe it's a coincidence.

48:55.760 --> 48:57.519
Could be.

48:57.520 --> 48:59.919
Makes me think you don't like me.

48:59.920 --> 49:02.799
No, it's not that, it's just...

49:02.800 --> 49:05.519
A widow needs time.

49:05.520 --> 49:08.839
Time for what?

49:08.840 --> 49:10.879
Time.

49:10.880 --> 49:12.999
I'm sorry, it's just...

49:13.000 --> 49:15.279
it's been two years.

49:15.280 --> 49:16.679
I grew up right there, Avigal.

49:16.680 --> 49:18.479
Every day, I saw you.

49:18.480 --> 49:22.241
We never talked, but I saw you.

49:25.640 --> 49:29.519
I know I'm not from a Rebbish home,

49:29.520 --> 49:33.088
Avigal, but I'm...
I'm a good person.

49:34.840 --> 49:37.959
Not right now.

49:37.960 --> 49:39.879
If not now, when?

49:39.880 --> 49:42.519
I have to go, Dovi.
Sorry, I can't be late.

49:42.520 --> 49:44.210
See, you're always in a rush.

49:45.040 --> 49:47.879
Make sure you're home before dark.

49:47.880 --> 49:50.686
Why? It's not Shabbos.

51:25.160 --> 51:27.759
Did you attend yeshiva?

51:27.760 --> 51:29.439
Me?

51:29.440 --> 51:32.959
No. No.

51:32.960 --> 51:34.959
How long do you have?

51:34.960 --> 51:37.079
An hour.

51:37.080 --> 51:39.965
An hour and a half.

51:44.920 --> 51:49.799
You know, I didn't expect
to see you again so soon.

51:49.800 --> 51:53.359
I had a doctor's appointment.

51:53.360 --> 51:54.846
Oh.

52:00.360 --> 52:01.439
You like to read?

52:01.440 --> 52:02.641
Mm-hmm.

52:03.800 --> 52:05.279
Have you read that one?

52:05.280 --> 52:07.209
I'm not supposed to.

52:08.440 --> 52:10.483
But you did, right?

52:11.960 --> 52:15.359
I had to get rid of all my
books when I got married.

52:15.360 --> 52:19.451
Well, men have never
wanted women to read.

52:37.480 --> 52:40.159
Who's this? Your mother?

52:40.160 --> 52:41.879
Mm-hmm.

52:41.880 --> 52:44.479
She's pretty.

52:44.480 --> 52:46.079
What was she like?

52:46.080 --> 52:48.408
Like?

52:50.200 --> 52:52.759
She was just a woman

52:52.760 --> 52:56.646
who never got the breaks.

52:58.040 --> 52:59.730
Here we go.

53:00.400 --> 53:02.399
- Here, let me.
- I was going to...

53:02.400 --> 53:04.559
Debone it?
I don't mind.

53:04.560 --> 53:07.519
It's kosher.

53:07.520 --> 53:09.085
I'll get the...

53:19.880 --> 53:21.366
You show me how you do it.

53:24.240 --> 53:26.559
Hold down the fish with your fork.

53:26.560 --> 53:30.321
Take your spoon, no rough edges.

53:33.200 --> 53:34.759
Tease the spoon

53:34.760 --> 53:38.239
under the flesh, gently.

53:38.240 --> 53:41.279
Lifting the flesh away
from the skeleton

53:41.280 --> 53:44.563
until you have a whole filet.

53:48.920 --> 53:51.043
Then flip it over.

53:52.640 --> 53:56.686
Then grab the tail that is still
attached to the skeleton.

53:58.440 --> 54:02.690
And like a zipper, pull it off.

54:08.080 --> 54:09.999
What about the head?

54:10.000 --> 54:12.879
It's kosher.

54:12.880 --> 54:15.242
It reminds you to look forward.

54:16.040 --> 54:18.919
A real fish-eater eats the cheeks.

54:18.920 --> 54:20.690
They're the delicacy.

54:26.840 --> 54:29.479
Hmm?

54:29.480 --> 54:31.523
For me?

54:39.600 --> 54:42.644
Il boccone del re.

54:43.320 --> 54:45.170
That's "the king's bite."

54:48.160 --> 54:50.886
I knew you weren't a Virgil.

54:52.720 --> 54:55.639
Fioravante. What does that mean?

54:55.640 --> 54:56.919
Flower.

54:56.920 --> 55:00.599
What kind of flower?

55:00.600 --> 55:02.928
Rudbeckia maxima.

55:05.040 --> 55:07.039
That's a cabbage leaf coneflower.

55:07.040 --> 55:10.999
A big six-foot plant with
big blue-green leaves

55:11.000 --> 55:13.079
and bright yellow flowers.

55:13.080 --> 55:14.959
And a big schnoz?

55:14.960 --> 55:17.359
It's just a showpiece.

55:17.360 --> 55:19.608
It doesn't really work.

55:21.920 --> 55:24.039
When I was in...

55:24.040 --> 55:26.519
sixth grade,

55:26.520 --> 55:28.599
I used to sit next to this girl.

55:28.600 --> 55:30.439
She was Jewish.

55:30.440 --> 55:32.759
Good.

55:32.760 --> 55:36.599
She had beautiful thick brown hair.

55:36.600 --> 55:40.559
And I would only look
at her straight on

55:40.560 --> 55:43.491
because I had seen my nose
in a three-way mirror.

55:49.400 --> 55:50.679
You're a good cook.

55:50.680 --> 55:52.919
Thank you.

55:52.920 --> 55:55.919
For a man.

55:55.920 --> 55:58.199
Hmm.

55:58.200 --> 56:01.679
Do you have any family?

56:01.680 --> 56:04.121
Not anymore.

56:05.600 --> 56:09.119
And you're not lonely?

56:09.120 --> 56:11.129
You get used to it.

56:13.960 --> 56:16.083
So this is what you do?

56:18.280 --> 56:19.686
I guess so.

56:21.920 --> 56:24.885
You bring magic to the lonely.

56:29.840 --> 56:32.639
That's one way to put it.

56:32.640 --> 56:35.320
And you get paid for it.

56:36.960 --> 56:38.491
Sometimes.

56:43.280 --> 56:46.279
I don't have much time left.

56:46.280 --> 56:48.323
Festina lente.

56:51.400 --> 56:54.444
Hurry slowly, Avigal.

56:57.920 --> 57:00.726
I like when you say my name.

57:03.600 --> 57:05.848
Rudbeckia maxima.

57:07.600 --> 57:09.239
You're going down, Papa Mo.

57:09.240 --> 57:11.319
I'm killing you.
We should be playing for money.

57:11.320 --> 57:13.439
You're not going to
get me out, old man.

57:13.440 --> 57:15.399
- (COCO GROWLS)
- (MURRAY LAUGHS)

57:15.400 --> 57:16.879
Okay, you only missed it by a foot.

57:16.880 --> 57:19.239
Turn around. More, more, more.

57:19.240 --> 57:21.639
Okay, ready?

57:21.640 --> 57:22.759
Strike two.

57:22.760 --> 57:24.919
- You like baseball?
- Yeah.

57:24.920 --> 57:26.999
The Spanish guys teach me.

57:27.000 --> 57:30.599
Not like I'm so great or anything,
but you know, I could play a little.

57:30.600 --> 57:32.399
Last game, we lost 20 to 3.

57:32.400 --> 57:35.719
Would've been worse, but they
got this mercy rule thing.

57:35.720 --> 57:37.039
(GRUNTS)

57:37.040 --> 57:40.479
What do you think?
Money laundering?

57:40.480 --> 57:42.039
Organ traffic?

57:42.040 --> 57:43.719
What?

57:43.720 --> 57:45.251
Avigal?

57:46.560 --> 57:48.399
That she should be
involved in such a thing.

57:48.400 --> 57:50.999
Organ traffic, where
do you get that stuff?

57:51.000 --> 57:52.519
- I read it...
- Stop talking.

57:52.520 --> 57:53.679
(MURRAY) Okay, you guys.

57:53.680 --> 57:55.803
This is going to be my spitter.

57:56.520 --> 57:59.159
- Yeah!
- Way to go, Cefus!

57:59.160 --> 58:00.850
Aah!

58:02.360 --> 58:04.039
Shh. Listen to me.

58:04.040 --> 58:05.399
Haitian Day parade...

58:05.400 --> 58:07.359
five bottle rockets I
took right to the chest.

58:07.360 --> 58:09.319
Did I cry? Did I make a sound?

58:09.320 --> 58:11.879
Not a peep. I took it.
Like a Sabra, I took it.

58:11.880 --> 58:14.401
Don't forget your envelope.

58:19.240 --> 58:20.799
You know, it's like candy,

58:20.800 --> 58:24.039
Having sex with you.

58:24.040 --> 58:27.839
You have one piece, and
you always want another.

58:27.840 --> 58:30.559
Do you have a girlfriend?

58:30.560 --> 58:33.119
I bet you don't say much.

58:33.120 --> 58:36.039
Get them into bed.
Make them happy.

58:36.040 --> 58:38.319
And then what?

58:38.320 --> 58:42.239
The Portuguese have a word for it.

58:42.240 --> 58:43.839
"Saudade."

58:43.840 --> 58:47.761
Yeah. A longing for something
that doesn't exist.

58:50.160 --> 58:53.399
I'm ready.

58:53.400 --> 58:54.839
Let's do the ménage.

58:54.840 --> 58:56.959
Call Bongo.

58:56.960 --> 58:59.119
Bongo? Oh yeah.

58:59.120 --> 59:00.679
Murray.

59:00.680 --> 59:02.719
Dan Bongo.

59:02.720 --> 59:04.839
Have a piece of dark chocolate.

59:04.840 --> 59:06.485
It's good for you.

59:09.920 --> 59:13.599
You know, you're top shelf.

59:13.600 --> 59:15.479
Hard to reach.

59:15.480 --> 59:17.489
That's what makes you so good.

59:28.760 --> 59:31.239
- Hi.
- Hello.

59:31.240 --> 59:34.808
Gather round.
These are your kids?

59:38.080 --> 59:40.119
We're going to divide
up into two teams

59:40.120 --> 59:42.084
and play baseball, okay?

59:45.280 --> 59:47.279
What do you think?

59:47.280 --> 59:49.079
- (MUTTERING)
- We don't play baseball.

59:49.080 --> 59:51.159
We're very serious people.
We have to study.

59:51.160 --> 59:53.679
Dovi plays.
Go, Twisters.

59:53.680 --> 59:55.359
It's a waste of time.

59:55.360 --> 59:56.839
Sometimes wasting time

59:56.840 --> 59:59.319
is healthy for the body.
It's good.

59:59.320 --> 01:00:02.279
I don't understand the
concept of competition.

01:00:02.280 --> 01:00:04.959
He doesn't understand the concept.

01:00:04.960 --> 01:00:06.759
You're overanalyzing.

01:00:06.760 --> 01:00:08.759
- Blacks against whites.
- No, no.

01:00:08.760 --> 01:00:11.359
- (YELLING)
- That's not going to happen.

01:00:11.360 --> 01:00:12.999
Not a good idea.
That's amazing.

01:00:13.000 --> 01:00:15.879
This is why fascism gets
a toehold all the time.

01:00:15.880 --> 01:00:18.159
You be on his side.
I want to break this up.

01:00:18.160 --> 01:00:21.919
I want to get a little Rainbow
Coalition here, guys, okay?

01:00:21.920 --> 01:00:25.363
Which one of these chosen people
do you want to play with?

01:00:49.360 --> 01:00:53.479
I couldn't wait to see you again.

01:00:53.480 --> 01:00:56.319
Ever see what's his name play?
Kevin Youkilis?

01:00:56.320 --> 01:00:58.039
The Red Sox?
You know, he's got a...

01:00:58.040 --> 01:01:01.050
You know, kind of a
shifty thing here.

01:01:02.520 --> 01:01:05.079
Here.

01:01:05.080 --> 01:01:07.039
For me?

01:01:07.040 --> 01:01:08.969
Yeah.

01:01:14.200 --> 01:01:16.119
Lower your head.
Bend over.

01:01:16.120 --> 01:01:18.999
Put your... put your head up.

01:01:19.000 --> 01:01:21.839
Down there. Ease up.
That's right. That's right.

01:01:21.840 --> 01:01:24.079
Okay, now,
I'll throw a couple to you.

01:01:24.080 --> 01:01:27.199
Bend over.
You look like a question mark.

01:01:27.200 --> 01:01:30.079
All right.

01:01:30.080 --> 01:01:32.282
- Ready?
- (BOY) Aim low!

01:01:34.000 --> 01:01:37.039
De la rosa sale el espino.

01:01:37.040 --> 01:01:40.799
Del espino sale la rosa.

01:01:40.800 --> 01:01:44.079
From the rose comes the thorn,

01:01:44.080 --> 01:01:47.284
from the thorn comes the rose.

01:01:58.240 --> 01:02:00.999
You're beautiful.

01:02:01.000 --> 01:02:03.282
You're really beautiful.

01:02:09.920 --> 01:02:11.884
- Avigal...
- Shh.

01:02:13.760 --> 01:02:16.639
You see me.

01:02:16.640 --> 01:02:20.279
I don't have to be someone else.

01:02:20.280 --> 01:02:22.801
That's enough.

01:02:26.000 --> 01:02:28.639
Kiss me.

01:02:28.640 --> 01:02:31.320
Let me look at you first.

01:02:41.080 --> 01:02:47.959
The mishna warns a married woman
never to appear outside her home

01:02:47.960 --> 01:02:50.479
with her hair visible.

01:02:50.480 --> 01:02:54.119
Your husband, Avigal,

01:02:54.120 --> 01:02:56.129
is gone.

01:03:45.880 --> 01:03:47.559
Well, is he coming or not?

01:03:47.560 --> 01:03:49.439
I'm so excited.

01:03:49.440 --> 01:03:51.079
(MURRAY) Absolutely.

01:03:51.080 --> 01:03:53.359
Yeah, we're completely ready.

01:03:53.360 --> 01:03:55.759
And the menage is on.

01:03:55.760 --> 01:03:57.879
Hey, I only wish I was there.

01:03:57.880 --> 01:04:00.599
Oh, Mr. Bongo.

01:04:00.600 --> 01:04:02.159
You're nasty.

01:04:02.160 --> 01:04:04.719
I'm... I am, but you're the
one who suggested it.

01:04:04.720 --> 01:04:07.879
Tell me. Have you ever...

01:04:07.880 --> 01:04:09.599
done it before? You know...

01:04:09.600 --> 01:04:11.439
ménage a trois?

01:04:11.440 --> 01:04:15.399
Yeah, in 1977, during a blackout.

01:04:15.400 --> 01:04:17.599
We... nobody could see anything.

01:04:17.600 --> 01:04:20.039
But it was still very pleasant.

01:04:20.040 --> 01:04:22.959
(CHUCKLES) You're naughty.

01:04:22.960 --> 01:04:26.199
Hey, you do remember that

01:04:26.200 --> 01:04:29.609
a threesome is 2,000 bucks.

01:04:34.560 --> 01:04:37.445
(HUMMING)

01:05:01.880 --> 01:05:03.639
What is this?

01:05:03.640 --> 01:05:05.599
I think you've got the wrong guy.

01:05:05.600 --> 01:05:07.599
I've already been circumcised.

01:05:07.600 --> 01:05:09.119
(MAN) Come on, come on, come on.

01:05:09.120 --> 01:05:10.799
Enough talk. In, in, in.

01:05:10.800 --> 01:05:13.759
Get in. In. Good.

01:05:13.760 --> 01:05:15.119
(MUTTERING)

01:05:15.120 --> 01:05:18.239
(MURRAY)
What'd I do? Break the dietary laws?

01:05:18.240 --> 01:05:20.119
(MAN) He's loose! He's moving!

01:05:20.120 --> 01:05:22.079
He's on the loose!
He's on the run!

01:05:22.080 --> 01:05:23.327
Get him, get him!

01:05:24.240 --> 01:05:27.159
A number of rabbis have
questions for you.

01:05:27.160 --> 01:05:28.959
Serious questions.

01:05:28.960 --> 01:05:30.559
We have your consent, right?

01:05:30.560 --> 01:05:33.399
I don't know what's going on.

01:05:33.400 --> 01:05:35.999
I want to speak to my
lawyer, Sol Hirsch.

01:05:36.000 --> 01:05:37.679
If it was up to me,
I'd tie you to a stone

01:05:37.680 --> 01:05:40.159
and leave you on the
side of the road.

01:05:40.160 --> 01:05:42.719
David had five smooth stones.

01:05:42.720 --> 01:05:44.759
(SPEAKS YIDDISH)

01:05:44.760 --> 01:05:46.599
I got this.

01:05:46.600 --> 01:05:47.999
Hey, look, that's not funny.

01:05:48.000 --> 01:05:52.079
I... I have no idea what
crime I've committed.

01:05:52.080 --> 01:05:54.079
Crime?

01:05:54.080 --> 01:05:55.319
There's a certain woman

01:05:55.320 --> 01:05:58.603
in our community, a widow,
a very special woman.

01:05:59.480 --> 01:06:03.359
I've never seen her
smile, not like this.

